arams` has at least 12 elements to avoid errors.\n\n---\n\n### Final function skeleton for `equation_v1`:\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\nMAX_NPARAMS = 12\n\ndef equation_v1(x0: np.ndarray, x1: np.ndarray, params: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    """\n    Calculate acceleration y for a nonlinear harmonic oscillator given position x0 and velocity x1.\n\n    The model includes:\n    - Constant offset\n    - Linear stiffness (position) and linear damping/driving (velocity)\n    - Quadratic nonlinearities in position and velocity\n    - Cubic nonlinearities in position and velocity\n    - Mixed nonlinear terms coupling position and velocity\n    - Fractional power damping-like term with sign preservation\n\n    Parameters:\n        x0 (np.ndarray): Position array.\n        x1 (np.ndarray): Velocity array.\n        params (np.ndarray): Array of at least 12 parameters controlling each term.\n\n    Returns:\n        y (np.ndarray): Acceleration array.\n    """\n    \n    if len(params) < MAX_NPARAMS:\n        raise ValueError(f"params must have at least {MAX_NPARAMS} elements")\n    \n    # Unpack parameters for clarity\n    c0 = params[0]   # constant offset\n    k1 = params[1]   # linear stiffness coefficient for x0\n    d1 = params[2]   # linear damping coefficient for x1\n    \n    k3 = params[3]   # cubic stiffness coefficient for x0^3\n    d3 = params[4]   # cubic damping coefficient for x1^3\n    \n    kx1x0 = params[5]  # mixed quadratic term: x0 * |x1|\n    \n    k2_x0_sq = params[7]  # quadratic stiffness term: x0^2\n    \n    d2_x1_sq = params[8]  # quadratic damping term: x1^2\n    \n    d_frac_pow = params[9]  # fractional power damping-like term with sign preservation\n    \n    mixed_x0_x1_sq = params[10]  # mixed nonlinear term: |x0| * x1^2\n    \n    mixed_x0_sq_x1 = params[11]  # mixed nonlinear term: |x0|^2 * sign(x1)\n\n    \n    y = (\n        c0 \n        + k1 * x0 \n        + d1 * x1 \n        + k3 * np.power(x0, 3) \n        + d3 * np.power(x1, 3